Abstract: Beaches in Florida, Georgia and South Carolina braced for the arrival of Tropical Storm Beryl, which made landfall late Sunday.
Snippet: Beaches in Florida, Georgia and South Carolina braced for the arrival of Tropical Storm Beryl, which made landfall late Sunday.
LeadParagraph: Beaches along the southern Atlantic coast were closed on Sunday, and visitors and residents in some low-lying regions were told to seek higher ground as Tropical Storm Beryl threatened to upset holiday weekend plans for thousands of beachgoers.

Headline.Main: Tropical Storm Interrupts Holiday Plans in Southeast
